items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

**Casting Call: ‚ÄúTHE RAT BASTARD STORY‚Äù (Stop-Motion Short)** 

We‚Äôre looking for an actor in their **late 20s to mid-40s** to play **The Artist** ‚Äî an eccentric, obsessive painter whose studio descends into chaotic madness when a mischievous rat (puppet) appears.

This is a **stop-motion production**, so the role requires someone **comfortable with stop-motion animation acting**, using **exaggerated physicality and expressions** to bring the character to life frame by frame.

**Details:**
* **Location:** Coventry
* **Filming:** Early November 2025
* **Compensation:** Unpaid role, but travel and catering costs covered

**Requirements:**
* Strong physical acting and comedic timing
* Comfortable performing exaggerated reactions for stop-motion capture
* Able to portray frustration, chaos, and dark humor

The rat is a puppet ‚Äî all interaction will be with puppetry.

IF INTERESTED, PLEASE EMAIL: bonvicinil@coventry.ac.uk

**CASTING CALL - EXTRAS X 2 - SOCIAL MEDIA VIDEO **

We are now casting for 2 x extras for our upcoming social media shoot on the 13th October, located in Central London. This is a speaking role (non-scripted), and we are searching for people who are comfortable discussing financial topics with an interviewer. 

An understanding of your own finances (and finance in general) and speaking about it comfortably is a must, as is the ability to ride a bike! You‚Äôll be filmed riding a bike for a short distance, so a good level of fitness is required.

**Age:** Under 45

**Gender/Ethnicity: **This is open to all ‚Äì we‚Äôre looking for the right energy, not a specific look.

**Tone:** This will not be too serious or formal ‚Äì this is a playful, public-facing stunt.

**Pay:** ¬£300 (travel is not included unfortunately, so would best suit those living in London)

**Date:** 13th October, potentially 2-3 hours (late morning / early afternoon)

Please send very recent headshots and any examples you might have to [casting@feral-films.com](mailto:casting@feral-films.com)

Thanks very much!

Spaces are limited by design - only 2 left!

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

items.text:
**CASTING CALL - EXTRAS X 2 - SOCIAL MEDIA VIDEO **

We are now casting for 2 x extras for our upcoming social media shoot on the 13th October, located in Central London. This is a speaking role (non-scripted), and we are searching for people who are comfortable discussing financial topics with an interviewer. 

An understanding of your own finances (and finance in general) and speaking about it comfortably is a must, as is the ability to ride a bike! You‚Äôll be filmed riding a bike for a short distance, so a good level of fitness is required.

**Age:** Under 45

**Gender/Ethnicity: **This is open to all ‚Äì we‚Äôre looking for the right energy, not a specific look.

**Tone:** This will not be too serious or formal ‚Äì this is a playful, public-facing stunt.

**Pay:** ¬£300 (travel is not included unfortunately, so would best suit those living in London)

**Date:** 13th October, potentially 2-3 hours (late morning / early afternoon)

Please send very recent headshots and any examples you might have to [casting@feral-films.com](mailto:casting@feral-films.com)

Thanks very much!

items.summary:
**CASTING CALL - EXTRAS X 2 - SOCIAL MEDIA VIDEO **

We are now casting for 2 x extras for our upcoming social media shoot on the 13th October, located in Central London. This is a speaking role (non-scripted), and we are searching for people who are comfortable discussing financial topics with an interviewer. 

An understanding of your own finances (and finance in general) and speaking about it comfortably is a must, as is the ability to ride a bike! You‚Äôll be filmed riding a bike for a short distance, so a good level of fitness is required.

**Age:** Under 45

**Gender/Ethnicity: **This is open to all ‚Äì we‚Äôre looking for the right energy, not a specific look.

**Tone:** This will not be too serious or formal ‚Äì this is a playful, public-facing stunt.

**Pay:** ¬£300 (travel is not included unfortunately, so would best suit those living in London)

**Date:** 13th October, potentially 2-3 hours (late morning / early afternoon)

Please send very recent headshots and any examples you might have to [casting@feral-films.com](mailto:casting@feral-films.com)

Thanks very much!

items.text:
Hello,
We‚Äôre Speed Network Now ‚Äî we create structured networking experiences with a creative twist: every session is filmed, directed, and turned into professional material for participants.

We‚Äôre currently looking for actors, and creatives in London to join our upcoming video projects.

This is an unpaid collaboration, but you‚Äôll receive edited showreel clips, on-set photos, credits, and real networking visibility within a growing creative community.

It's a chance to meet important businesses in England 

If this sounds like something you would enjoy, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Thank you for your time and interest, send dm here or mary.speednetworknow@gmail.com
Speed Network Now

items.text:
We're so proud to be driving real change in the UK arts sector.

Now in its second year, the Ramps on the Moon Change Programme is supporting arts leaders across the UK to embed anti-ableism throughout their organisations.

Led by Mich√®le Taylor MBE and supported by Laura Twemlow at People Make it Work with an outstanding cohort of cultural change partners from Belgrade Theatre, Coventry Birmingham Hippodrome Derby Theatre Eastern Angles Theatre Company Headlong Lincoln Arts Centre Orange Tree Theatre Royal Shakespeare Company Sheffield Theatres Tall Stories National Theatre and Theatre Royal, Bury St. Edmunds

"The social model was explained clearly, and I finally understand it in depth."
"Great to connect with others facing the same challenges."

Learn more and follow the cohort‚Äôs journey: www.rampsonthemoon.co.uk

#AntiAbleism #DisabilityEquality #RampsOnTheMoon

message.text:
STILL FEEL LIKE YOUR NOT MOVING FORWARD AS AN ACTOR ??? 

Most actors spend years in classes and never learn the real fundamentals that get them work.

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we don‚Äôt just ‚Äútalk‚Äù about acting‚Ä¶. we train you like a professional. Our students go from their very first class to being on set in real films, learning more in weeks than many do in years.

Because you‚Äôre not a number here. You‚Äôre a future storyteller‚Ä¶.. and we‚Äôll show you how to become the actor casting directors remember.

üåü Spotlight Approved ‚Ä¢ üé• SAG Recognised ‚Ä¢ üé¨ Real Films ‚Ä¢ üé≠ Real Results

Message us now for in person , online or one to one classes.

LOCATION: Banbury, Oxfordshire, UK

PRODUCTION DATES: One weekend ‚Äì either 11‚Äì12, 18‚Äì19, or 25‚Äì26 October 2025

PAID, UNPAID OR PROFIT SHARE: Paid ‚Äì ¬£250 for 2 days + travel considered

ABOUT THE PROJECT:

Failsafe is a psychological short film currently in production with a professional crew. Directed by award-winning filmmaker, whose previous film Time Spent earned 23 awards, 22 nominations, and an 8.8 IMDb rating.

The final scenes are being cast for this dynamic and visually intense project, which will be submitted to national and international festivals and featured in Pro Movie Maker Magazine.

FEMALE LEAD

‚Ä¢ Age Range: 25‚Äì35

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

F√ºr eine Musical Show am Samstag, 21. M√§rz 2026 im Kurhaus Bad Herrenalb werden Statisten im Alter von 16 - 99 gesucht.

Die Statisterie wird mit kleinen Schauspieleinlagen, sowie Bewegungssequenzen in die Produktion integriert sein.

Gezeigt werden Ausschnitte aus Tanz der Vampire, K√∂nig der L√∂wen, Mamma Mia, Aladdin, The Greatest Showman, Grease u.v.m.

Die Proben finden 1x w√∂chentlich in Bad Herrenalb bei Karlsruhe statt.

Die Leitung des Showprojekts hat Sandra Maria Germann, die das Musical Ensemble Dance Charisma leitet und seit vielen Jahren national und international als Musicaldarstellerin, Schauspielerin und Choreographin t√§tig ist.

Wir freuen uns auf rege Teilnahme von ambitionierten Schauspielern und T√§nzern (m/w/d).

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

7x talent needed for a photo shoot about digital education and safety. Examples of roles that are featured: a gamer, an influencer, a modern logistics worker, & students learning about the digital space. 

SINGAPOREAN ONLY - all ethnicities

3x Female

4x Male 

SHOOT DATES

27 or 28 Oct 

6 or 7 Nov

Please send your head shots and other existing work to [esther@vitamin-change.com](mailto:esther@vitamin-change.com) with the subject heading: DIGITAL SAFETY SHOOT

Only those shortlisted will be contacted with additional information. Thank you!

items.text:
Web series titled Buried Lies, set in the United Kingdom, which explores life-changing secrets, intense emotions, and the raw truth people hide. Each episode revolves around characters confronting their past through confessions that affect their lives and the people around them.

We are seeking talented, expressive individuals ready to take on a variety of dramatic roles. All nationalities are welcome to apply.

PROJECT DETAILS:

Title: BURRIED LIES (Web Series)

Genre: Drama / Thriller

Locations:

London

Manchester

Liverpool

Edinburgh

Shooting Dates:

October 27th ‚Äì December 5th, 2025 (Flexible schedules possible) This is Tentative dates for Episode One Only

Usage: Web series for online streaming platforms and promotional content

Payment: ¬£200 ‚Äì ¬£350 per shooting day, depending on role and experience

MAIN CHARACTERS & EXAMPLES OF CONFESSIONS:

1. Emma (28) ‚Äì A young woman who confesses to having sabotaged her best friend‚Äôs career out of jealousy.

2. David (45) ‚Äì A corporate executive who admits to embezzling funds to cover personal debts.

3. Sophie (22) ‚Äì A college student revealing her involvement in an illegal online scheme that endangered others.

4. Mark (35) ‚Äì A father confessing to hiding the truth about a child‚Äôs paternity.

5. Leila (30) ‚Äì A mysterious woman confessing that she witnessed a hit-and-run accident and stayed silent.

6. James (40) ‚Äì A detective forced to confess to using illegal means to close a high-profile case.

7. Clara (50) ‚Äì A mother disclosing that she manipulated family inheritance to favor one child over another.

8. Ali (33) ‚Äì A young man confessing to secretly living a double life to escape financial troubles.

9. Nina (25) ‚Äì A nurse who reveals covering up a medical mistake that led to a patient‚Äôs death.

10. Supporting Roles: Friends, colleagues, strangers, investigators, and family members deeply affected by the confessions.

EXAMPLES OF CONFESSIONS IN THE SERIES:

"I let my friend take the fall for a crime I committed."

"I have been living a lie for the past five years to protect my reputation."

"I once stole confidential data from my employer for personal gain."

"I am not the biological parent of the child I raised as my own."

"I witnessed a murder but didn‚Äôt report it because I was too scared."

"I have been in contact with a dangerous person despite knowing the risks."

WHO CAN APPLY:

All nationalities

Age 18 ‚Äì 55

Prior acting experience preferred but not mandatory

Comfortable performing intense, dramatic scenes

Willing to travel within the UK to shoot in different locations

Available for full shoot dates or specific days as needed

TO APPLY:

Send your portfolio, recent photograph, showreel (if available), and contact information to:

Email: annasiller88@gmail.com 

Auditions will start from October 11th, 2025. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted directly.

**Castingopslag: Reklamefilm ‚Äì s√∏ges medvirkende 40+**

Hej alle,

Vi er en gruppe filmstuderende, der skal producere en **fiktiv reklamefilm for Folketinget**, som har til form√•l at f√• flere unge til at stemme.

Vi leder efter **m√¶nd og kvinder i alderen 40+** til at spille politikere i filmen.

Optagelserne finder sted **mandag d. 13. oktober i Helsing√∏r**.

Da der er tale om en skoleproduktion med lavt budget, kan vi desv√¶rre kun tilbyde et symbolsk honorar i form af 2 biografbilletter for dagen ‚Äì men vi lover god stemning, et professionelt set og en sjov oplevelse!

Hvis du har lyst til at v√¶re med, s√• send gerne en mail med:
* **Navn**
* **Alder**
* **Et billede**
* (Gerne) en kort video, hvor du siger disse to replikker ‚Äì de m√• gerne leveres med en frustreret tone:
1. *‚ÄúJeg forst√•r simpelthen ikke, hvorfor de unge ikke g√•r mere op i politik‚Ä¶‚Äù*
2. *‚ÄúDe fylder da gaderne med bannere og r√•b hele tiden?‚Äù*

Send det hele til: **adda-olsen@hotmail.com**

Vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra dig!

Bedste hilsner,

Frederikke

We are casting for a 3 month contract in Lagos, Nigeria. The engagement runs from early November through the end of January, working four nights per week in a nightclub setting.

We are looking for acts that are beautiful, elegant, and unusual.

Rigging is available.

We are particularly interested in:

Unusual LED acts
Foot archery acts
Unique or rare performance styles (fire can be used indoors)

Contract details:

Return flights provided
Working visa arranged
Accommodation provided in a secure villa (with tennis courts and swimming pool)
Driver included
Meals provided on work nights

If you have availability and an act you‚Äôd like us to consider, please comment in the thread below with your act details and a link or video.

Please do not send direct messages as these will not be responded to.

Thank you.

items.text:
Hi Everyone!

I'm Sam, a student filmmaker currently in pre-production for a college action/comedy short film and** I am looking for 3 actors.**

The film is based around two not‚Äëso‚Äësharp operatives for ‚ÄúThe Boss‚Äù debrief a failed pickup, shifting blame as flashbacks reveal how a simple job spiraled out of control.

I plan to start shooting around late October into November, with no exact dates planned yet.

This will be shot in and around Basildon, Essex.

The Characters:
* **Sonny**
A young (aged 20+) newcomer desperate to be taken seriously on their first job. Intelligent and strong‚Äëminded, quick to speak up against perceived wrongs - sometimes at the worst moment.
* **Vince**
A little older (aged 25+) and endlessly amused by chaos. Loud, funny, and distractible, but surprisingly capable when it counts.
* **The Boss**
Aged 20 +. Few words, all weight. Commanding, serious, and perpetually in control - at least in theory.

As this is a student project, this will be unpaid, unfortunately. This is a great opportunity for emerging actors looking to build their resumes. You‚Äôll also be credited for your work in the film.

I will of course share more details before the shoot, so don't worry.

If you are interested, please send me a quick email to **samuelh.moore@outlook.com**

Please make sure you include this info:

- Your Name

- Age

- Gender

- Where you live/location

- and a short 30 second self-tape of a comedic performance

Thank you!

STILL FEEL LIKE YOUR NOT MOVING FORWARD AS AN ACTOR ??? 

Most actors spend years in classes and never learn the real fundamentals that get them work.

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we don‚Äôt just ‚Äútalk‚Äù about acting‚Ä¶. we train you like a professional. Our students go from their very first class to being on set in real films, learning more in weeks than many do in years.

Because you‚Äôre not a number here. You‚Äôre a future storyteller‚Ä¶.. and we‚Äôll show you how to become the actor casting directors remember.

üåü Spotlight Approved ‚Ä¢ üé• SAG Recognised ‚Ä¢ üé¨ Real Films ‚Ä¢ üé≠ Real Results

Message us now for in person , online or one to one classes.

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

items.summary:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

We're on the lookout for six talented actors to bring this project to life! While these roles are unpaid, we will cover travel expenses and provide meals. 
Plus, this is a fantastic opportunity to enhance your showreel or portfolio!

If you‚Äôre passionate about acting and eager to dive into a vibrant creative environment, we want to hear from you!

Auditions are in-person on Saturday, November 22nd, in Swinton, Manchester.

Don‚Äôt forget to include a link to your Spotlight or Backstage profile. We can‚Äôt wait to find the incredible talent that will shine in our project!

items.text:
Christmas Panto Casting Call 

Troubadour Productions (TIE and care homes shows for over 20 years) are casting three actors to tour schools and some care homes in London and South East in December.

There will be four days rehearsal (probably late November) plus approx. 16 tour days in December 2025 with this multi-roling, musical production of "Beauty and the Beast."

At least one member of the cast **must** be a car owner/driver to ‚Äúdrive‚Äù the tour so car owners/drivers will have a slight advantage in the casting.

Ideally, actors should be able to live at home and commute daily to an agreed pick up point. At the end of the day the driver will then return the actors to a mutually convenient drop off point.

Each actor will receive a flat fee of ¬£1400 and the driver will receive an extra ¬£320.00 (¬£20 per day) for driving the tour. The driver will have **all** petrol paid.

The Roles

Beauty

Ideally Female. Should be an experienced singer and to be able to dance or move well. Beauty is an intellectual, very kind and helpful. She is close to her father and will do anything for him.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume and singing reel please

Required Skills:
* Voice Style: Singing
* Dance: Movement

 

Louis/Nannette

This is a multi-roling opportunity. A versatile performer required to play Beauty's father, Louis Dubois and the housekeeper in the Beast's castle, Nanette. An actor who is capable of creating different characters by using different voices and ways of moving. Louis should preferably be played with a slight French accent. He is hardworking and a single father. Nanette can be played as a 'dame' character, very flamboyant. A comedy role. There is also a chicken in the production, which may be performed by this actor. The chicken doesn't speak, just clucks.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume/voice reel

Required Skills:

 

The Beast/Monsieur Livre

A versatile performer to play the Beast and Monsieur Livre, the librarian who hopes to win Beauty's heart. Any age or ethnicity. We perform to schools and care homes, and in some of these venues, the Beast may need to be toned down and maybe more comical than angry. In some other shows, the Beast can show their anger and frustration by shouting and making the audience jump. The Beast also has a softer side when he gets to know his 'prisoner', Beauty. The Beast wears a wig with horns, with the face uncovered. Monsieur Livre only appears at the start of the show. He is very persistent. Can be played for laughs. It is important that the actor can create two very different characters by changing voices and movement. There is also the part of Alouette, the chicken, which could be portrayed by this actor. Skin character experience preferred, but not absolutely necessary. The chicken has no lines, but is very expressive.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume

Required Skills:
* Voice Style: Singing
* Dance: Movement

 

The Beast/Monsieur Livre

A versatile performer to play the Beast and Monsieur Livre, the librarian who hopes to win Beauty's heart. Any age or ethnicity. We perform to schools and care homes, and in some of these venues, the Beast may need to be toned down and maybe more comical than angry. In some other shows, the Beast can show their anger and frustration by shouting and making the audience jump. The Beast also has a softer side when he gets to know his 'prisoner', Beauty. The Beast wears a wig with horns, with the face uncovered. Monsieur Livre only appears at the start of the show. He is very persistent. Can be played for laughs. It is important that the actor can create two very different characters by changing voices and movement. There is also the part of Alouette, the chicken, which could be portrayed by this actor. Skin character experience preferred, but not absolutely necessary. The chicken has no lines, but is very expressive.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume

Required Skills:
* Voice Style: Singing
* Dance: Movement

 

 

 

Dates & Locations

Rehearsals  4 days (non-consecutive) between November to early December in Milford, South Guilford.

Tour runs 10-23 Dec. (Sundays are off) in South London, Hampshire, Surrey, Middlesex, Sussex and Essex, England. Note: There may be some additional dates added if production gets busier. The actors will tour from their homes and meet up with the actor or driver to perform.

Additional: At least one of the team needs to be a driver who has their own car, and is willing to use it as a company vehicle. Troubadour productions pay for all petrol in advance. An additional fee of ¬£20 per day (for use of car and driving) will be paid to the driver for performance days.

 

Auditions will be on Zoom or other virtual platforms. Production will want to see a 2-minute modern monologue. This can be targeted to the panto job or can be a piece they already know, but no Shakespeare or restoration comedy please.

We would also would like to hear a song sung to a backing track as a reel. Preferably musical theatre or possibly nostalgic pop. Music is heavily featured in our shows, and we use backing tracks, so it is important that we know you can sing to them accurately. Production shall start to see auditionees from 6 Oct. onwards.

Special Instructions:

For consideration, talent must note in the submission where they are based. This is very important when assessing for possibility of actors being able to meet up. If talent has any friends of relatives in any of the above areas, also state those towns as it may increase the likelihood of being chosen for an audition. Production doesn't have multiple teams touring different parts of the UK, just casting the one team of three for London and Home Counties.

Our actors will need a current and enhanced DBS certificate, but we will help you apply for and we will pay for one if needed.

If interested in applying please e-mail a cv, headshot and singing reel to a backing track please with answers to the following questions:

1)     Do you drive

2)     Do you have a car that you could use for the tour

3)     Where are you based (please state the name of the town or borough (of London)

4)     Do you have a DBS (We will get you one if not!)

Please e-mail applications to
tom@troubadourproductions.co.uk

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Sir Percy Shorter - chairman of the BMA, quite upper class and not too tall (Mid 40s+

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall

Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 

Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.

Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 

The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

***CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT FILM!!!***

***UNPAID & NON-UNION***

Location: Vancouver, BC

Film Dates: November 14th, 15th, & 16th with 2 rehearsals to be scheduled after casting

Casting "Confession", a student short film set in the late 1950s about a closeted devout Catholic who confesses his secret love for his priest during confession, only to discover the priest feels the same way.

Father Elias D'Arcy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic priest who has been the head of Jacob‚Äôs church for a few years now, developing a close relationship with his parish. He came from a poor family, the child of Irish immigrants and the eldest of 6, he‚Äôs always had a nurturing nature to him and often helped others to the detriment of his own mental capacity. A closeted homosexual, Elias has delved deep into his religion and joined the priesthood to stave off any romantic connection, unwilling to come to terms with his sexuality.

Jacob McCarthy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic and closeted gay man, his struggles with his raised religion and his sexuality being the catalyst for his story. He forced himself to marry a girl he was raised going to church with to promote a sense of normalcy and to please his family as the eldest child and only son expected to carry on the family name and reputation. He's unhappy with the life he chose to live for other people, feeling as though no one really knows him for who he truly is.

Actors will be compensated with a copy of the film, credit, and a meal every day of filming.

For audition scheduling and sides, please contact a.culp@infocusfilmschool.com
